In the *Issue Navigator*, perform the *Advanced Searching*. JQL Query example:

{code}
project = TEST AND fixVersion = 1 AND resolution is EMPTY
{code}

It will display *This query is too complex to display in Simple mode*. Further tests was made using the following JQL query:

{code}
project = TEST and resolution is EMPTY
{code}

The message is still displayed. The explanation to this is that the when you have the *resolution* set to *EMPTY*, somehow it is able to show the result correctly but because since the actual *resolution* is *Unresolved* and there is no *EMPTY* resolution, somehow it is translated to be a complex query.

Kindly refer to screenshots attached.

